{
  "texts": [
    "The model was built using histopathology images as the original dataset, and positive images were rotated to balance the number of IDC negative and IDC positive images.",
    "During the model evaluation, this method achieved an average accuracy of 91.6%.",
    "Celik et al.",
    "[23] developed a model for detecting invasive ductal carcinoma (IDC) using the BreakHis breast cancer dataset and utilizing ResNet-50 and Dense-Net-161 pre-trained deep learning techniques.",
    "The aim was to detect IDC through the use of these pre-trained models."
  ]
}